body:
See my pull request for this same change on the 3.1 branch, tenderlove made a comment and I responded. https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4407

@jrochkind I'm totally on board with you.  rails new should give you an app that can run immediately.  New users are already overwhelmed by all of the pieces of Ruby and Rails (bundle, rake, gems, these are all totally new concepts to them).  Forcing them to go to the github page for execjs, pick one of the options listed there, and figure out how
 to implement their choice is a lot to ask a newbie that just wants to see the Welcome to Rails page.  Good suggestion on adding a comment about what therubyracer is.  I'll add that, and see if I can figure out how to add the commit to the pull request.
